Git is a distributed version control system that tracks file versions. It's often used to control source code by programmers collaborating on software development.


git --version
pwd(present working directory)
ls
git status


CONFIG SETTINGS
--global(iske through git humare system pe configuration file rakhta h global settings pe and git ko pata h woh file kaha h so woh automatically usko dekh lega and then global level pe we r making an email and similar for name)
git config --global user.email "arunisharma.placement@gmail.com"
git config --global user.name "Aruni"
to check the config: git config --list


git config --global init.defaultBranch <name>
git branch -m <name>

CREATING REPO
git status
git init (role is to get the hidden folder .git n the folder tracking is started)   
ls -la (to check if we have .git folder)
ls -l


Staging
git add <file> <file2>
or git add . (all files)
git status
(but rn commits r not done yet)

git rm --cached <file>  (to unstage the file)



COMMIT
git commit -m "commit message"
git status



LOGS
git log  ()
git log --oneline  ()



CHANGE DEFAULT CODE EDITOR (which is VIM)
git config --global core.editor "code --wait"



